\brief This function configures all relevant IPs from Power Off to Power Standby. \details This function configures all relevant IPs from Power Off to Power Standby. This function should be called during RFE initialization \pre RFE power supplies should be enabled \param [in] rfeRole - The RFE role (standalone/leader/follower) \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true, On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures all relevant IPs and selected Rx\Tx IPs from Power Standby to Power On. \details This function configures all relevant IPs and selected Rx\Tx IPs from Power Standby to Power On. This function should be called before using RFE e.g. before calibration, acqusition and RF Bist phases. \pre RFE was set to Power Standby using rfeSwPwrMngr_pwrOff2Stby() or rfeSwPwrMngr_pwrOn2Stby() \param [in] rfeRole - The RFE role (standalone/leader/follower) \param [in] txSelect - Selection of any combination of TX 1/2/3/4 \param [in] rxSelect - Selection of any combination of RX 1/2/3/4 \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true, On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures all relevant IPs and selected Rx\Tx IPs from Power On to Power Standby. \details This function configures all relevant IPs and selected Rx\Tx IPs from Power On to Power Standby. This function should be called after RFE was used e.g. after calibration, acqusition and RF Bist phases. \pre RFE was set to Power On using rfeSwPwrMngr_pwrStby2On() \param [in] rfeRole - The RFE role (standalone/leader/follower) \param [in] txSelect - Selection of any combination of TX 1/2/3/4 \param [in] rxSelect - Selection of any combination of RX 1/2/3/4 \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true, On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures all relevant IPs from Power Standby to Power Off. \details This function configures all relevant IPs and selected Rx\Tx IPs from Power Standby to Power Off. This function should be called when RFE is to be set to power down mode (experimental feature). \pre RFE was set to Power Standby using rfeSwPwrMngr_pwrOn2Stby() or rfeSwPwrMngr_pwrOff2Stby() \param [in] rfeRole - The RFE role (standalone/leader/follower) \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true, On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures all relevant TSense IPs from Power On to Power Off. \details This function configures all relevant TSense IPs from Power On to Power Off. This function should be called when RFE is to be set to power down mode (experimental feature). \pre RFE was set to Power On using rfeSwPwrMngr_pwrStby2On() \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true, On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures all relevant TSense IPs from Power Off to Power On. \details This function configures all relevant TSense IPs from Power Off to Power On. This function should be called when RFE is to be set to power down mode (experimental feature). \pre RFE power supplies should be enabled \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true, On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures LLDO PDC IP from Power Off to Power On and reconfigures PDC. \details This function configures LLDO PDC IP from Power Off to Power On and reconfigures PDC as IP reset happens. This function should be called during RFE power management. \pre RFE power supplies should be enabled \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true, On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL

\brief This function configures LLDO PDC IP from Power On to Power Off. \details This function configures LLDO PDC IP from Power On to Power Off. This function should be called during RFE power management. \pre RFE power supplies should be enabled \param [in,out] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER - Error handling parameter: On success #RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR is true, On failure #RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR is true \return NIL \post NIL \ingroup NIL
